-- UK's FCA appoints Hoggett to head investment banking
-- 
-- Wed Mar 12, 2014 07:04AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, March 12 (Reuters) - Britain's financial regulator has appointed Julia Hoggett to head supervision of investment banks, drawing on her experience as a managing director at Bank of America Merrill Lynch.

Hoggett is currently managing director for debt capital markets products at Bank of America <BAC.N> and will start her new job in early May, reporting to Will Amos, the FCA's director of wholesale banking and investment management.